overview: "The user initiated a review of a recently implemented interactive
  sleep questionnaire, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work.
  The agent performed a comprehensive code review, identifying several gaps and
  missing features, which were then prioritized into a detailed action plan. The
  agent then proceeded to implement the first two high-priority items:
  integrating a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference, complete with
  critical safety warnings for high scores, and adding explicit detection and
  reporting for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea). This involved
  modifications across multiple files, including type definitions, validation
  schemas, UI components, and report generation logic for both web and PDF
  outputs."
